            Sykdomspulsen
            Sykdomspulsen is a real time analysis and diseases surveillance system designed and developed at the Norwegian Institute of Public Health (NIPH/FHI).
            «Data» is not useful by itself. Data must be cleaned, analysed, and the results delivered to stakeholders. An effective outbreak response requires this in near real-time.
            Sykdomspulsen’s goal is to achieve this.
            We receive data from more than 15 data sources
            2 000 000 000+ rows of data og results (1TB)
            1000 database tables
            500 000+ analyses per day
            500+ automatic reports per day
            
            
            Sykdomspulsen core
            Sykdomspulsen Core is the free and open-source backbone of Sykdomspulsen Analytics.
            
            
            splverse
            splverse is a number of R packages that have been developed by the Sykdomspulsen team to help with infectious diseases surveillance.
            
            
            Sykdomspulsen for kommunehelsetjenesten
            Dersom du er kommuneleger eller statsforvalter og leter etter nettsiden Sykdomspulsen for kommunehelsetjenesten må du klikke her
